    .page-header
      h1 About Upcoming
    
    p. 
      #[strong Upcoming] is a simple way to share and discover interesting events from your friends, followers, and the artists and organizations you care about.
      
    p.
      Upcoming wasn't built for event promoters, organizers, or venues &mdash; it was built for you. Add the stuff you're most excited about going to, recommend interesting stuff you find, and follow people with tastes like your own.
              
    p Everything on Upcoming was added by the community, not from feeds or scraped from around the web. It's a curated list of events from the people that use it every day.
      
    p Upcoming will never be comprehensive, and it's not for everybody. That's okay.
      
  
    h2 History
    p.
      Launched in 2003, before Flickr or Facebook, Upcoming was the first site to use a social network for event discovery. After two years, Upcoming was acquired by Yahoo, running for a decade before Yahoo shuttered it in 2013.
      
