  .col-xs-12.col-sm-10.col-sm-offset-1.col-md-8.col-lg-6
    p.
      Shortly after they shut it down, Yahoo offered to sell the domain back to me, an 
      unprecedented move for a former acquisition. 
      
    p.
      I decided to launch a <a href="https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/waxpancake/the-return-of-upcomingorg/description">Kickstarter project</a> to gauge interest in bringing Upcoming back from the dead. With the incredible support and infinite patience of <a href="/about/backers">1,787 backers</a>, I rebuilt Upcoming from scratch, restored the <a href="http://archive.upcoming.org/">event archive</a>, and relaunched the community in March 2017.
      
    p Thank you for believing in it.
          
    h2 Who
    p.
      Upcoming was developed and designed by me, <a href="http://waxy.org/">Andy Baio</a>. I started Upcoming in 2003, and was joined a year later by my friends <a href="https://twitter.com/lhl">Leonard Lin</a> and <a href="https://twitter.com/getluky">Gordon Luk</a>, who came on board as co-founders.
    
    p. 
      Gordon moved on to other projects, and Leonard is a technical advisor for the latest incarnation.
      
    p.
      If you'd like to contribute to Upcoming's development, you can join the party <a href="https://github.com/upcoming">over at GitHub</a>.
  
  
    h2 Thanks
